21:24.863 --> 21:28.450
- No. They went with the other guy.
- I told you to kiss ass more.

21:28.575 --> 21:31.995
- Angela, please.
- I'm sure something will open up soon at ULA.

21:32.120 --> 21:34.356
Yeah, well, one can
only hope, can't one?

21:34.456 --> 21:37.692
In the meantime, I'm glad that
you're still slumming it here with us.

21:37.792 --> 21:40.320
You city college lot
don't pull any punches do you?

21:40.420 --> 21:43.089
- We will go 16 rounds with anyone.
- Bring it on.

21:58.063 --> 21:59.856
Asshole.

22:00.774 --> 22:02.233
Asshole.

22:02.359 --> 22:05.320
Never let me hear you
say that word, Jake.

22:05.820 --> 22:09.766
The word is "ahh's-hole" not "aah's-hole."
Can you say "ahh's-hole?"

22:09.866 --> 22:13.244
- Asshole.
- Yes, elongate the A.

22:14.037 --> 22:15.330
There we go.

22:15.789 --> 22:18.166
I'll get them. I'll get them.

22:20.502 --> 22:23.672
- Mama!
- No, mama is at work.

22:25.090 --> 22:27.926
- She'll be back later.
- Mama.

22:32.555 --> 22:36.017
No, that's Hummer. Hummer.

22:36.434 --> 22:38.186
Well done. Hummer.

22:38.311 --> 22:39.629
- Pull over.
- What?

22:39.729 --> 22:42.983
- Pull over! Listen to this voicemail.
- I can't pull over.

22:45.527 --> 22:46.928
<i>I thought he was saying "mama,"</i>

22:47.028 --> 22:50.990
<i>and then I realized he was pointing
at one of those absurdly oversized tanks</i>

22:51.116 --> 22:55.245
<i>driven no doubt by some idiot
with an absurdly undersized penis.</i>

22:55.370 --> 22:57.622
- This is not an oversized car.
- <i>All right.</i>

22:58.123 --> 22:59.666
He knows.

23:07.132 --> 23:10.243
- Hey there, sexy. Where are you?
- I'm in New York.

23:10.343 --> 23:12.245
Honey, do I look chunky?

23:12.345 --> 23:14.472
Didn't mean to call you sexy.
Wrong person.

23:15.890 --> 23:18.435
No, I look good.

23:19.018 --> 23:20.562
<i>Very funny. Is Kate there?</i>

23:20.687 --> 23:23.715
She's not back yet, still banking.
Busy counting things.

23:23.815 --> 23:26.443
Well, tell her to call me
right, right away,

23:26.568 --> 23:28.862
because I have something
really big to tell her.

23:28.987 --> 23:32.223
No secrets in the family. Pray tell.

23:32.323 --> 23:34.351
<i>I can't believe
that I'm about to tell you...</i>

23:34.451 --> 23:38.647
Richard, I don't know
why this is so hard for me.

23:38.747 --> 23:41.733
I've been trying
to tell you now for weeks.

23:41.833 --> 23:45.587
- Alan's asked me to marry him.
- I'm in love with somebody else.

23:46.629 --> 23:48.281
You're what?

23:48.381 --> 23:52.035
We're getting married! Don't act
so surprised that somebody asked me.

23:52.135 --> 23:54.220
- Are you on the phone?
- Who is it?

23:54.345 --> 23:56.973
- Who are you talking to?
- Answer the question. Who is it?

23:57.098 --> 24:00.226
- I just did!
- Who's on the phone?

24:01.186 --> 24:02.587
- Hello?
- Kate! Kate!

24:02.687 --> 24:06.316
- I have to call you back.
- What? Hello?

24:07.025 --> 24:11.971
I was just, I mean... I was
really young, okay? Really young.

24:12.071 --> 24:15.767
Not that you're not, of course.
But I really thought that I loved you,

24:15.867 --> 24:18.311
but clearly I was working
through daddy issues.

24:18.411 --> 24:23.900
And then I got pregnant, and you
were just trying to do the right thing.

24:24.000 --> 24:28.780
And you've been a really good father, but
let's face it, you never really loved me.

24:28.880 --> 24:32.408
- But Brian does.
- Brian? Brian?

24:32.508 --> 24:34.494
That little idiot from the office?

24:34.594 --> 24:39.207
He likes to talk to me about start-ups
and acquisitions and exit strategies.

24:39.307 --> 24:41.876
I mean, all the stuff that you think
is so boring about me.

24:41.976 --> 24:43.837
It is boring. God.

24:43.937 --> 24:48.149
Why do you have to be so
goddamn English? Talk to me!

24:48.441 --> 24:53.221
You can leave me,
but I am not leaving that boy.

24:53.321 --> 24:55.031
Brian.

24:55.698 --> 24:57.450
Richard,

24:57.575 --> 24:59.953
why can't you just talk to me?

25:11.005 --> 25:13.783
Now, I know two years in the pool house

25:13.883 --> 25:16.744
makes me look a little a nut,
but I'll say two things.

25:16.844 --> 25:19.914
First, your mom and Brian
hated me being there,

25:20.014 --> 25:22.475
which was the most wonderful
incentive to stay.

25:22.600 --> 25:24.227
And secondly...

25:25.895 --> 25:28.314
I wanted to be close to you.

25:28.982 --> 25:31.109
Good morning.

25:32.443 --> 25:35.405
I think you're going
to want to see this.

25:35.571 --> 25:39.200
- Oh, let me see it.
- Is the big bad professor awake yet?

25:39.325 --> 25:43.354
<i>Jake to Dad. Breaker, breaker.
You got your ears on?</i>

25:43.454 --> 25:44.998
- Okay.
- <i>Are you awake?</i>

25:45.123 --> 25:49.627
- It's Jakey. Just a second.
- <i>Get up! Are you having a sleepover?</i>

25:50.628 --> 25:53.448
Hi, Jakey! Good morning.

25:53.548 --> 25:56.075
- Where are you?
- <i>Can I come and play?</i>

25:56.175 --> 25:57.844
Just a second, Jakey.

25:57.969 --> 26:00.246
- Hey.
- Hi!

26:00.346 --> 26:03.558
Would you mind just skedaddling for now?
It's my son.

26:03.683 --> 26:06.894
Your son? I love kids! I babysit!

26:07.020 --> 26:09.339
- Sorry about this. The perils of parenthood.
- It's okay.

26:09.439 --> 26:11.149
- Come and see me during the week.
- When?

26:11.274 --> 26:14.068
- Make it a surprise.
- Oh, I love surprises! Okay, I will.

26:14.193 --> 26:16.429
Okay, good-bye.

26:16.529 --> 26:18.973
- Who was that?
- Oh, just a friend of mine.

26:19.073 --> 26:22.076
Very busy lady. She had to leave.
There you go.

26:23.202 --> 26:24.954
Aren't these uncomfortable?

26:25.079 --> 26:28.416
That's why girls love it when you
take them off. Let's get some pancakes.

26:28.541 --> 26:30.168
Dad, get on with it.

26:30.752 --> 26:33.463
So there we were.

26:34.714 --> 26:36.466
And then...

26:36.758 --> 26:38.409
last week...

26:38.509 --> 26:40.953
everything went pear-shaped.

26:41.053 --> 26:43.431
I have the papers you asked for.

26:44.849 --> 26:48.978
- Will that be all, professor?
- For now, yes, thanks.

26:51.898 --> 26:53.608
Great.

26:54.358 --> 26:56.110
Excuse me.

26:57.278 --> 26:59.347
Newest member of the TA
of the month club?

26:59.447 --> 27:01.641
How dare you insinuate such a thing?

27:01.741 --> 27:05.244
- You have a visitor. Be nice.
- Send them in.

27:06.204 --> 27:07.622
Thank you.

27:11.417 --> 27:14.821
- Professor Pickard, what a delight!
- How's your father these days?

27:14.921 --> 27:18.424
- Loving life. He is happy as a clam.
- That's good to hear.

27:18.549 --> 27:21.844
Well, I received your application
for the position at the University.

27:21.969 --> 27:25.765
I was in the area, so I thought I would
just pop by and invite you to a soirée

27:25.890 --> 27:27.708
- I'm giving tomorrow.
- Splendid.

27:27.808 --> 27:29.685
The faculty will be there, of course.

27:29.810 --> 27:33.397
I thought it might be a good idea if you do
come by and just sort of butter them up.

27:33.523 --> 27:36.692
Not me, by the way.
I consider myself lavishly buttered.

27:36.817 --> 27:38.428
Oh, well, that's good to know.

27:38.528 --> 27:41.405
- So we'll see you there.
- Wouldn't miss it for the world.

27:42.907 --> 27:45.226
"Dustin Kalarney"
just sold its 5 millionth copy.

27:45.326 --> 27:47.662
- You're unbelievable.
- What?

27:47.787 --> 27:52.525
Here I am, splayed out like an open-faced
sandwich so we can have a baby,

27:52.625 --> 27:55.544
- and all you care about...
- Mr. Sloan.

27:56.003 --> 27:58.364
Would you mind signing a copy
of your book for me?

27:58.464 --> 28:02.451
- Of course. Did you like it?
- Are you kidding? It was great.

28:02.551 --> 28:05.763
Really? Is that Desiree two Es or one E?

28:07.390 --> 28:09.308
What the hell was that for?

28:09.433 --> 28:12.520
Oops, it slipped.
Can I have my phone back, please?

28:14.105 --> 28:16.465
There you go, you can do it.
Just concentrate.

28:16.565 --> 28:20.611
- Nice big swing. That's it.
- Dad, I suck.

28:20.736 --> 28:23.723
No, you don't, you don't.
You look great, just eye on the ball.

28:23.823 --> 28:27.560
Who's here! Jakey, what up, dawg?
Yo, give me some love.

28:27.660 --> 28:29.228
Blow it up. Blow it up.

28:29.328 --> 28:31.439
- Jellyfish sting!
- Jellyfish sting!

28:31.539 --> 28:33.958
Lots of love. We were just
playing a little ball here.

28:34.083 --> 28:36.377
- Right. Sorry, sorry.
- That's all right. Okay.

28:37.295 --> 28:40.031
What are you doing? You're a righty.
You got to switch your hands around.

28:40.131 --> 28:43.759
- Come around there. Bat up!
- Eye on the ball. Hit it to Dad!

28:44.510 --> 28:47.705
Sorry, Dad! Are you okay? Are you okay?

28:47.805 --> 28:51.642
I'm okay, son. I'm all right.
Just... occupational hazard.

28:51.767 --> 28:55.271
- That looks pretty bad.
- No, this. It's okay.

28:55.396 --> 28:57.231
Jakey!

28:57.481 --> 28:58.774
- Hey.
- Hey.

28:58.899 --> 29:02.553
- Did you remember Atlanta?
- Yeah. No? Atlanta?

29:02.653 --> 29:05.322
- Brian and I, four days, conference.
- Got it.

29:05.448 --> 29:08.325
- We leave the day after tomorrow.
- Good. Sounds good. I'll be there.

29:08.451 --> 29:10.036
- No, you'll be here.
- I'll be here.

29:10.161 --> 29:12.063
- Yeah. Here's Jakey's schedule.
- Great.

29:12.163 --> 29:14.482
I left a copy in your room
and another one on the fridge.

29:14.582 --> 29:17.026
- All right. That's good.
- So, yeah.

29:17.126 --> 29:19.086
I'm on it. Jawohl!

29:20.296 --> 29:22.048
Okay.

29:23.174 --> 29:25.326
No, I understand,

29:25.426 --> 29:29.889
but I strongly believe that three slaves
is enough. It's enough. Come on.

29:39.190 --> 29:41.066
You!

29:45.988 --> 29:47.823
Dr. Collins!

29:51.952 --> 29:53.245
Son of a bitch!

29:57.917 --> 29:59.835
Yeah!

30:00.753 --> 30:02.546
Jesus.

30:04.089 --> 30:05.841
Come in.

30:06.258 --> 30:09.053
- Shouldn't you be at work?
- Yeah, covering the Asian markets.

30:09.637 --> 30:12.456
Oh, hey, by the way, I can get you
in on a pretty sweet no-load.

30:12.556 --> 30:15.835
These guys are killing it right now. I can
get you 15%, 18%. Just say the word.

30:15.935 --> 30:18.187
The word is no.
What is it you want? I'm busy.

30:18.312 --> 30:20.815
This letter came for you. It's about
your green card. I'm sorry.

30:20.940 --> 30:23.467
- I opened it before I saw who...
- Just read it, Brian, thank you.

30:23.567 --> 30:26.554
- I mean, you've opened it. Just read it.
- All right. "This is your final warning.

30:26.654 --> 30:29.306
If you and your spouse fail to attend
your interview next week,

30:29.406 --> 30:32.368
deportation proceedings
will be initiated."

30:35.538 --> 30:39.041
Blimey, mate. Looks like you could be
in a spot of bother with the Bobbies.

30:40.543 --> 30:43.737
Keep working on the accent, Brian.
Close the door on the way out.

30:43.837 --> 30:46.173
- Cheerio.
- Shut up.

30:46.298 --> 30:49.885
I love the dentist.
I'm not drooling, am I?

30:50.719 --> 30:52.763
Hello, Mr. Haig.

30:52.888 --> 30:55.516
You can't drink alcohol
when taking this medication.

30:55.641 --> 30:56.642
- Really?
- Yes.

30:56.767 --> 30:57.710
- No?
- No.

30:57.810 --> 31:00.212
Absolutely not. Wouldn't dream of it.
Thank you so much.

31:00.312 --> 31:01.714
- No alcohol.
- Good.

31:01.814 --> 31:03.632
- We'll see you soon.
- Can't wait.

31:03.732 --> 31:05.901
Look forward to it. Thank you so much.

31:06.026 --> 31:07.636
- No alcohol.
- No alcohol.

31:07.736 --> 31:09.655
- I mean it.
- I mean it, too.

31:16.370 --> 31:19.315
Okay, let's go this way.
Any time you feel like it,

31:19.415 --> 31:22.918
- jump in and lavish me with praise.
- Copy that.

31:23.043 --> 31:25.921
- So glad you could make it!
- Oh, thank you!

31:26.046 --> 31:27.506
- Here you are.
- Thanks. Wonderful.

31:27.715 --> 31:32.369
Please, help yourself to refreshments.
My wife made her famous cheese balls.

31:32.469 --> 31:35.247
Please be sure to try one
and compliment her accordingly.

31:35.347 --> 31:37.224
Will do.

31:38.851 --> 31:42.855
There are some very, very important
people here. I'd like you to meet them.

31:42.980 --> 31:46.050
And they are your kind
of people, Richard.

31:46.150 --> 31:48.152
Come this way.

31:51.030 --> 31:54.642
My dear colleagues,
this is Richard Haig.

31:54.742 --> 31:57.186
This is Professor Vale, Bates, Berg,

31:57.286 --> 31:58.996
- Ang and Professor Jones.
- Hello.

32:03.208 --> 32:05.461
Can we do that again?
I forgot your names already.

32:06.712 --> 32:10.240
It is a damn shame we didn't hire you,
what was it, three years ago?

32:10.340 --> 32:14.178
Three years, two months, 17 days.
But who's counting?

32:14.636 --> 32:16.538
- You know, I met your father once.
- Oh, yeah?

32:16.638 --> 32:20.334
He delivered a fascinating lecture,
a retort to Terry Hearst,

32:20.434 --> 32:23.729
a hermeneutical reading
of Milton's "Paradise Lost."

32:23.854 --> 32:26.565
- Wish I'd been there for that one.
- Where are you from in England?

32:26.690 --> 32:29.568
- And are you a Rich or a Dick?
- I'm a Richard.

32:29.693 --> 32:32.654
- Your father took a structural stance...
- You know, the missus and I,

32:32.780 --> 32:35.032
we love it over there,
we go every summer.

32:35.157 --> 32:38.327
- You do? Great.
- Cheers again, matey.

32:38.452 --> 32:41.563
Richard, I want to let you know
that these fervent minds here

32:41.663 --> 32:44.583
have taken great care looking over
your application material.

32:44.708 --> 32:47.586
Never trust an Englishman
who doesn't drink, Richie boy.

32:47.711 --> 32:49.989
- Syllabus...
- ...epistemological level.

32:50.089 --> 32:51.256
Academics. Yup, yup, yup.

32:51.381 --> 32:55.244
- I do have one small question for you.
- This one's the biggest yapper of them all.

32:55.344 --> 32:59.181
How are the Romantics relevant
to today's students?

33:03.352 --> 33:04.962
You want me to answer this question now?

33:05.062 --> 33:09.258
I'm sure we'd all enjoy hearing
just a taste of one of your lectures.

33:09.358 --> 33:11.777
- A taste.
- A mere amuse-bouche is all.

33:12.277 --> 33:15.614
Why not the whole meal? Why don't you
come down and see me in action?

33:15.739 --> 33:18.267
- I happen to be free on Thursday.
- Christ, what about that?

33:18.367 --> 33:20.869
I see you've already met my wife.

33:24.456 --> 33:28.527
I'm just going to go outside for a moment
here, and just jump in front of a bus.

33:28.627 --> 33:30.779
Where are you going?
You didn't even say goodbye!

33:30.879 --> 33:32.798
That's true.

33:33.757 --> 33:35.551
Bye!

33:35.926 --> 33:38.053
I wonder if he was flirting with me.

33:38.679 --> 33:40.597
Oh, my God.

33:44.935 --> 33:46.937
Oh, shit.

33:49.565 --> 33:51.567
Oh, bollocks.

34:12.295 --> 34:13.405
Shit.

34:13.505 --> 34:17.050
Good evening, Officer. Oh, boy.
Have I been drinking?

34:18.427 --> 34:21.013
I drink every night. How about you?

34:21.722 --> 34:24.308
Can't we all just get along?

34:36.695 --> 34:38.405
Thanks.

34:41.699 --> 34:44.143
Thanks again for bailing me out.

34:44.244 --> 34:47.539
- And for the silent treatment.
- Don't talk to me.

34:54.880 --> 34:56.547
I still can't believe it.

34:56.672 --> 34:59.259
- Can't believe what?
- I wasn't talking to you.

34:59.384 --> 35:03.830
And I wasn't talking to you,
my darling little fornicating ex-wife.

35:03.930 --> 35:05.999
- Shut up, Richard.
- Alan dumped me.

35:06.099 --> 35:10.020
What a small world.
My wife did exactly the same thing.

35:10.145 --> 35:12.314
She used to adore me.

35:12.939 --> 35:15.150
Where, oh, where did the love go?

35:15.275 --> 35:17.444
She turned 30 and wised up.

35:17.736 --> 35:21.056
So, what's going on?
Why are you here, Olivia?

35:21.156 --> 35:23.684
- Thank you so much for helping out.
- It's the least I can do.

35:23.784 --> 35:26.186
- Helping out? Helping out with what?
- I needed to know

35:26.286 --> 35:30.023
that Jake was going to be looked after,
fed, and driven by a responsible person

35:30.123 --> 35:32.876
- with a valid driver's license.
- Fine. Why her?

35:33.001 --> 35:36.171
Livvy offered to come
at a very difficult time for her

35:36.296 --> 35:39.324
to bail us out of the mess
that you put us in.

35:39.424 --> 35:41.009
You know what?

35:41.134 --> 35:45.706
- I've had enough of this.
- You know, you say "I" a lot.

35:45.806 --> 35:50.627
Really? Well, I know that Jake
loves having you around.

35:50.727 --> 35:53.880
But I'm getting phone calls
from your immigration attorney

35:53.980 --> 35:56.466
because you don't ever bother
to call him back.

35:56.566 --> 36:00.762
I can't be in your life anymore.
I'm enabling your degenerate behavior.

36:00.862 --> 36:03.907
And what is the point
of all this right now?

36:04.032 --> 36:07.619
Richard, if you want me to pretend
like we're happily married

36:07.744 --> 36:11.706
so you can stay in this country,
you better get it together.

36:25.554 --> 36:27.706
- Yeah?
- <i>Gotcha.</i>

36:27.806 --> 36:30.625
- <i>I woke you up, didn't I?</i>
- Dad, is that you?

36:30.725 --> 36:34.880
You know, there are no time zones
in China. Did you know that?

36:34.980 --> 36:37.774
<i>The whole bloody country
is on Peking time,</i>

36:37.899 --> 36:40.569
<i>and that's the way it should be.</i>

36:40.694 --> 36:44.306
- We should all be on Peking time.
- <i>Don't be a dumb prat.</i>

36:44.406 --> 36:47.726
The whole world
should be on London time.

36:47.826 --> 36:50.370
Okay. What do you want, Dad?

36:52.914 --> 36:55.400
- How's the little turd?
- Don't call him that.

36:55.500 --> 36:59.070
Come on,
you're far too bloody sensitive.

36:59.170 --> 37:02.115
<i>All right, great to hear from you, Dad.</i>

37:02.215 --> 37:05.302
Why don't you go badger Joan? Okay?

37:05.427 --> 37:06.995
<i>She's not here.</i>

37:07.095 --> 37:11.141
Shit. Okay. I've got to go. Goodbye.

37:28.158 --> 37:30.285
Richard Haig?

37:31.328 --> 37:32.412
Thank you.

37:40.795 --> 37:43.131
So, your interview is Monday.

37:43.256 --> 37:46.301
This is the fourth quarter now, two minute
warning, you got no timeouts left.

37:46.426 --> 37:47.869
What the hell are you talking about?

37:47.969 --> 37:52.932
If your ex-wife won't show up to your
interview, it's going to be Hail Mary time.

37:53.058 --> 37:54.726
Okay?

37:55.977 --> 37:59.397
- So, did you get a full-time job?
- Doing my best.

37:59.522 --> 38:01.967
Have you recently joined
any terrorist organizations?

38:02.067 --> 38:05.487
Applied all over. Fingers crossed.

38:08.365 --> 38:10.617
Have you ever been arrested?

38:13.286 --> 38:16.289
- DUI.
- When? How many years ago?

38:16.414 --> 38:19.859
Friday? I mean, they can't kick me
out of the country for that, can they?

38:19.959 --> 38:22.921
- Jakey's a US citizen.
- You see the people in my waiting room?

38:23.046 --> 38:25.824
The kid born here, the parents, illegal.

38:25.924 --> 38:28.551
They're deporting the parents!

38:28.843 --> 38:31.930
Oh, yeah, it's game seven,
win or go home time.

38:32.555 --> 38:36.226
All right, well, if you join
a recovery program now...

38:36.559 --> 38:37.877
What, recovery?

38:37.977 --> 38:41.256
You do the 10 mandated sessions
the court's going to give you for the DUI.

38:41.356 --> 38:44.092
- 10? That's going to take me weeks!
- Hell week, baby. Two-a-days.

38:44.192 --> 38:46.678
You get your ex-wife to your interview
and you get a great job.

