I think I left my phone in the car.

01:00:22.279 --> 01:00:24.306
- Hi!
- You're naked.

01:00:24.406 --> 01:00:27.868
If you're wondering where Jake is,
he's at a sleepover with Josh.

01:00:28.160 --> 01:00:31.288
- Why are you naked?
- Richard's sleeping in his house.

01:00:31.413 --> 01:00:34.416
- I'm just gonna go and swim.
- Unbelievable.

01:00:37.628 --> 01:00:39.964
Hey, how's the lecture coming?

01:00:40.089 --> 01:00:43.217
I've passed kidney stones
with greater ease.

01:00:43.968 --> 01:00:48.597
Well, don't overthink it.
Just be honest, pithy, simple.

01:00:49.098 --> 01:00:53.978
You know something? I think you're the first
woman I've ever really been friends with.

01:00:54.103 --> 01:00:56.756
Well, that's a little sad, Richard,
but very touching.

01:00:56.856 --> 01:01:00.276
What brought about this sudden
onset of sincerity?

01:01:02.903 --> 01:01:05.765
I slept with someone,

01:01:05.865 --> 01:01:07.491
and...

01:01:08.075 --> 01:01:10.411
it actually meant something.

01:01:10.619 --> 01:01:13.147
Well, that's great. Who?

01:01:13.247 --> 01:01:14.957
Olivia.

01:01:16.125 --> 01:01:20.404
Are you kidding? Richard, why don't you go
down to your Green Card appointment,

01:01:20.504 --> 01:01:23.365
take out your samurai sword,
and disembowel yourself?

01:01:23.465 --> 01:01:26.660
What is wrong with you?
Are you trying to get deported?

01:01:26.760 --> 01:01:30.080
- I mean, Kate is going to kill you!
- Kate's not going to know about it, is she?

01:01:30.180 --> 01:01:32.349
I mean, I'm not going to tell her,
and Olivia's not going to tell her.

01:01:32.474 --> 01:01:37.187
They are sisters, Richard,
close sisters, and close sisters talk.

01:01:41.275 --> 01:01:43.319
You better move.

01:01:53.537 --> 01:01:56.165
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.

01:02:03.631 --> 01:02:04.798
- Kate, hi.
- Hey!

01:02:04.923 --> 01:02:08.052
- How's everything? Good?
- Olivia told me everything.

01:02:08.218 --> 01:02:10.287
Oh, she did?

01:02:10.387 --> 01:02:13.265
I think it's awesome
that she started writing.

01:02:15.309 --> 01:02:17.686
And she said you were really nice
to her when I was away.

01:02:17.811 --> 01:02:20.147
Oh, wonderful.

01:02:20.648 --> 01:02:24.343
You know... I know I've been
kind of a bitch to you lately.

01:02:24.443 --> 01:02:25.444
Oh, that's okay.

01:02:25.569 --> 01:02:30.032
Threatening not to come to your green card
meeting was totally out of line. I'm sorry.

01:02:30.157 --> 01:02:33.202
Yeah, live and let live,
forgive and forget, all of that.

01:02:33.327 --> 01:02:35.729
- We're cool?
- We are so cool.

01:02:35.829 --> 01:02:38.357
Okay. Do you want
to get me some lemonade?

01:02:38.457 --> 01:02:39.692
- Good idea.
- Thanks.

01:02:39.792 --> 01:02:42.461
Okay. Great.

01:02:52.221 --> 01:02:54.223
You smoke?

01:02:58.977 --> 01:03:02.815
- I can't stop thinking about last night.
- Nor can I.

01:03:04.608 --> 01:03:06.635
- We have to tell her.
- No, no, no.

01:03:06.735 --> 01:03:08.946
- This is not good timing. Olivia, Olivia.
- Dad?

01:03:09.071 --> 01:03:11.265
That's gone to your head. Get back
in the bush. Get behind the bush.

01:03:11.365 --> 01:03:14.518
There's a funny old man here
that wants to see you.

01:03:14.618 --> 01:03:16.286
What?

01:03:17.246 --> 01:03:19.023
Dad, what are you doing here?

01:03:19.123 --> 01:03:23.418
Why in buggering hell
have you been ignoring my calls?

01:03:24.044 --> 01:03:27.698
Oh, hello, this must be the Yank totty!

01:03:27.798 --> 01:03:30.175
Kate, my father.

01:03:30.801 --> 01:03:32.953
Oh, my goodness, Mr. Haig!

01:03:33.053 --> 01:03:36.165
It's so nice to meet you!

01:03:36.265 --> 01:03:39.585
- Sorry, I'm soaking wet.
- I need a shower anyway.

01:03:39.685 --> 01:03:42.880
Oh, and who is this other vision
of loveliness?

01:03:42.980 --> 01:03:46.550
I'm Olivia. I'm Kate's sister.

01:03:46.650 --> 01:03:48.986
Blimey. Bookends.

01:03:49.403 --> 01:03:51.989
Well, come inside,
I'll make you up a room.

01:03:52.114 --> 01:03:54.658
No, no, no, it's okay. Dad, come with me.
Come to the guesthouse.

01:03:54.783 --> 01:03:58.036
- We've got plenty of rooms.
- No, that's okay. Dad, come with me.

01:03:58.162 --> 01:04:00.564
- Are you sure?
- You're staying with me. I promise you.

01:04:00.664 --> 01:04:02.791
- Nice to meet you!
- You too!

01:04:02.916 --> 01:04:07.713
- Why exactly are you here?
- I'm visiting you and the little turd...

01:04:07.838 --> 01:04:13.660
- Fella. What's it bloody look like?
- Well, I don't really know. I mean...

01:04:13.760 --> 01:04:16.330
Jake, meet your grandfather.

01:04:16.430 --> 01:04:18.582
Yeah. I'm your granddad.

01:04:18.682 --> 01:04:21.627
I've got something for you
that I brought all the way from England.

01:04:21.727 --> 01:04:27.466
Would you like to see it?
Now that is a model of "HMS Defiance."

01:04:27.566 --> 01:04:29.902
God, Dad. You never let me
used to touch that.

01:04:30.027 --> 01:04:32.321
- What?
- Okay, I'll be right back.

01:04:32.446 --> 01:04:34.848
Hey! Wait a minute, where are you going?

01:04:34.948 --> 01:04:38.101
You can't bear to be in the same room
with me for two minutes, is that it?

01:04:38.201 --> 01:04:41.121
- No, that's not it, Dad, not at all!
- Can I keep it?

01:04:41.413 --> 01:04:44.458
Of course you can bloody keep it.
It's yours!

01:04:44.583 --> 01:04:48.587
But don't put it in the bath,
because it'll sink.

01:04:51.632 --> 01:04:53.926
- Hey, cool!
- Where should we put it? Here?

01:04:54.051 --> 01:04:56.595
- On the top!
- Yes, on the top!

01:04:58.513 --> 01:05:00.582
Hello, my lovelies.

01:05:00.682 --> 01:05:04.603
All I'm asking is, can you wait
till Monday morning at 11:00?

01:05:05.479 --> 01:05:07.189
Why?

01:05:07.314 --> 01:05:09.608
My green card interview.

01:05:10.984 --> 01:05:12.803
After that...

01:05:12.903 --> 01:05:14.905
you can...

01:05:15.530 --> 01:05:17.824
tell her what you like, okay?

01:05:36.093 --> 01:05:37.761
Dad...

01:05:38.345 --> 01:05:41.348
- I need to go pee.
- Come on, then.

01:05:41.723 --> 01:05:44.835
Hey, where the bloody hell
are you two going? Come on, hey!

01:05:44.935 --> 01:05:49.089
- We're going to go for a pee, Dad.
- Come on, whip it out. Come on!

01:05:49.189 --> 01:05:52.634
- Dad, you can't pee off the pier.
- Jake, who are you going to listen to?

01:05:52.734 --> 01:05:57.347
Your dad, who, for some buggering reason
has turned into a boring old fart,

01:05:57.447 --> 01:06:00.826
or your grandfather,
who's lived a rich and full life

01:06:00.951 --> 01:06:03.578
and doesn't take shite from anybody?

01:06:05.622 --> 01:06:08.108
You! Sorry, Dad.

01:06:08.208 --> 01:06:12.362
There you go, come on up here.
There you go. Up you go.

01:06:12.462 --> 01:06:16.700
Come on, you too.
If you're still my son, that is.

01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:21.263
All right, on three. One, two, three.

01:06:21.388 --> 01:06:24.391
Yeah! That's it.

01:06:29.396 --> 01:06:33.567
Well, somebody had
their vitamins this morning.

01:06:35.652 --> 01:06:38.347
You know, there are coconuts over there!

01:06:38.447 --> 01:06:40.657
Great isn't it? There you go.

01:06:41.741 --> 01:06:45.645
Beautiful. Oh, dear.
All right, all right, all right.

01:06:45.745 --> 01:06:49.708
That's good stuff.
Put on some tunes, guys?

01:06:50.208 --> 01:06:54.838
Oh, look at this. This is paradise, man.
You've ended up in paradise!

01:06:54.963 --> 01:06:58.300
You know, they must be freezing
their bollocks off in England.

01:07:01.219 --> 01:07:03.638
Why are you really here?

01:07:10.562 --> 01:07:14.858
Joan left me. Silly cow.

01:07:15.525 --> 01:07:19.613
Well, I'm sorry. Truly.

01:07:20.447 --> 01:07:25.185
Well, that makes me feel so much better.

01:07:25.285 --> 01:07:30.315
I mean, God almighty, thank you
for those profound words of sympathy.

01:07:30.415 --> 01:07:33.401
Well, it's a lot more than you
ever said when Kate left me.

01:07:33.501 --> 01:07:35.420
Well, I warned you about her!

01:07:35.545 --> 01:07:38.131
She was a rampant little Yankee trollop.

01:07:39.633 --> 01:07:42.577
You know what, Dad?
Of course Joan left you.

01:07:42.677 --> 01:07:46.623
You're a misanthropic, misogynistic asshole
who doesn't give a fuck about anybody,

01:07:46.723 --> 01:07:51.127
least of all the poor saps who you got
to marry you in the first place.

01:07:51.227 --> 01:07:54.606
Is that it? Is that all you've got?

01:07:54.731 --> 01:07:59.069
And you did it all in the name
of some misguided credo called fun.

01:07:59.194 --> 01:08:01.304
Which you brainwashed me
with in the first place.

01:08:01.404 --> 01:08:03.990
Guys, dig this song!

01:08:04.282 --> 01:08:05.367
Bugger off.

01:08:08.745 --> 01:08:11.189
That's it then, is it, boy wonder?

01:08:11.289 --> 01:08:15.068
So you finally got it
off your chest, have you?

01:08:15.168 --> 01:08:17.337
You know what, Dad?

01:08:17.837 --> 01:08:20.631
Why don't you just bugger off for once?

01:08:20.756 --> 01:08:22.300
For once...

01:08:22.425 --> 01:08:25.845
why don't you be the one to bugger off?

01:08:55.750 --> 01:08:58.545
Brian, go back to my wife.

01:08:58.877 --> 01:09:00.613
Go on.

01:09:00.714 --> 01:09:04.283
Go on, just... just go back.

01:09:04.384 --> 01:09:06.411
Thank you for that wonderful sharing.

01:09:06.511 --> 01:09:10.807
Seriously, this has been
absolutely a marvelous session.

01:09:10.932 --> 01:09:14.310
I've learned so much.
Give yourselves a big hand. Everybody.

01:09:14.435 --> 01:09:17.020
Wendy, I was wondering
if you could sign my form

01:09:17.147 --> 01:09:19.732
to show that I've done the 10 sessions?

01:09:21.234 --> 01:09:23.778
I'm sorry, Richard, I can't.

01:09:25.363 --> 01:09:30.033
Why? I mean, I came,
I did the whole "I'm an alcoholic..."

01:09:30.410 --> 01:09:33.621
But it's not about
just saying the words.

01:09:33.746 --> 01:09:36.791
You have to actually mean them.

01:09:42.881 --> 01:09:45.425
Great seeing you. Thanks so much.

01:09:48.051 --> 01:09:50.180
Cindy, right?

01:09:50.305 --> 01:09:53.725
I just spent the last week listening
to that drivel so some witless little ninny

01:09:53.850 --> 01:09:56.836
won't sign a piece of paper
to say I'm an okay kind of guy.

01:09:56.936 --> 01:10:00.356
Absolute bollocks. Sorry, excuse me.

01:10:01.274 --> 01:10:03.510
Hey, you want to get a drink?
Actually, maybe not.

01:10:03.610 --> 01:10:06.237
I've got a grueling lecture in an hour.

01:10:06.362 --> 01:10:09.199
How about a joint?
Just kidding, bad joke.

01:10:09.324 --> 01:10:13.536
I didn't want my son to find it.
I don't touch the stuff. It's my dad's.

01:10:13.912 --> 01:10:15.788
Likes to puff.

01:10:16.456 --> 01:10:19.876
- Good luck with your lecture.
- Thank you.

01:10:27.967 --> 01:10:31.121
I want you all to imagine
you're at Cambridge University.

01:10:31.221 --> 01:10:33.556
The year is 1807.

01:10:33.681 --> 01:10:35.917
You walk across the quad
of Trinity College.

01:10:36.017 --> 01:10:40.380
Into the lecture hall, you find
your fellow classmate, Lord Byron,

01:10:40.480 --> 01:10:45.193
who, in defiance
of college rules about dogs,

01:10:45.318 --> 01:10:48.446
has brought a bear to class instead.

01:11:03.086 --> 01:11:05.296
You know what?

01:11:05.880 --> 01:11:07.757
Forget about that.

01:11:07.882 --> 01:11:11.636
Why are the Romantics relevant today?

01:11:14.973 --> 01:11:16.724
Honestly...

01:11:16.849 --> 01:11:18.518
they're not.

01:11:19.978 --> 01:11:21.880
Stacy got it right.

01:11:21.980 --> 01:11:26.134
And Dwight, he can't stop thinking
about home runs and fastballs

01:11:26.234 --> 01:11:28.945
when he reads Byron and Coleridge.

01:11:32.824 --> 01:11:34.492
Because...

01:11:35.284 --> 01:11:37.370
we're teaching words.

01:11:38.496 --> 01:11:40.123
Words.

01:11:40.915 --> 01:11:43.459
But we're not teaching meaning.

01:11:45.044 --> 01:11:47.130
I got it all wrong.

01:11:47.547 --> 01:11:52.009
I can tell you about Byron and his bear,
Wordsworth falling in love with his cousin,

01:11:52.135 --> 01:11:55.455
Coleridge falling in love with cocaine.

01:11:55.555 --> 01:11:58.433
I can tell you what's behind
the words from them,

01:11:59.058 --> 01:12:02.478
but I can't tell you what's behind
those words for you.

01:12:03.354 --> 01:12:06.899
Because this class is about you

01:12:07.024 --> 01:12:09.610
learning to find your own meaning.

01:12:10.945 --> 01:12:13.030
Your own voices.

01:12:15.241 --> 01:12:19.103
Go read the poems.
But know this, that at this moment,

01:12:19.203 --> 01:12:24.233
you are the Romantics,
you are the relevant ones.

01:12:24.333 --> 01:12:28.780
Let Byron, Coleridge, Wordsworth
inspire you to do your thing,

01:12:28.880 --> 01:12:30.631
to go your own way.

01:12:30.757 --> 01:12:33.676
Stacy, quit texting.
Call him, right now.

01:12:34.135 --> 01:12:38.164
Dwight, go play ball.
Ignore anyone who says no, you can't.

01:12:38.264 --> 01:12:42.810
Follow your hearts. Do good things,
be bold, and, above all else...

01:12:44.103 --> 01:12:45.980
stick it to the man.

01:12:48.900 --> 01:12:52.136
Well, Dad, I totally fucked up
my audition lecture.

01:12:52.236 --> 01:12:56.474
I stuck it to them all right.
I stuck it to myself in the process, too.

01:12:56.574 --> 01:13:01.062
Hey, listen, you silly old sod,
you just bolted before I could apologize.

01:13:01.162 --> 01:13:04.190
Why are you so thin-skinned these days?

01:13:04.290 --> 01:13:07.001
All right, call me back.

01:13:21.933 --> 01:13:24.961
$4,000 should cover it.

01:13:25.061 --> 01:13:26.212
What?

01:13:26.312 --> 01:13:30.608
Your Mustang, Richard, it's got Sienna Red
paint there all over the back fender.

01:13:30.733 --> 01:13:32.635
Unmistakable.

01:13:32.735 --> 01:13:36.514
1954 MG TFs do not come cheap,
my friend.

01:13:36.614 --> 01:13:38.991
Absolutely not. Can I give you a check?

01:13:39.116 --> 01:13:41.118
I would prefer cash.

01:13:44.622 --> 01:13:47.358
Wanted to be the first
to congratulate you.

01:13:47.458 --> 01:13:50.570
Welcome to the English department,
University of Los Angeles.

01:13:50.670 --> 01:13:52.697
Yes!

01:13:52.797 --> 01:13:55.658
Oh, good. Oh, thank you, boss.

01:13:55.758 --> 01:13:57.927
I guess we'll do the other side as well.

01:13:58.052 --> 01:14:00.454
- Let's go have a pint.
- A pint of what? Oil?

01:14:00.554 --> 01:14:04.642
A pint of what... Witty.
I'll always laugh at your jokes.

01:14:13.067 --> 01:14:16.345
I got the job. ULA!
Knocked it out of the ballpark.

01:14:16.445 --> 01:14:19.265
- Congratulations!
- Home run! Fantastic!

01:14:19.365 --> 01:14:22.894
And I feel fantastic about you
and what we did, making love.

01:14:22.994 --> 01:14:24.562
No, listen please. Hear me out.

01:14:24.662 --> 01:14:27.023
Kate and I have been separated
for two years.

01:14:27.123 --> 01:14:30.067
Why should we feel bad?
We're grownups, you know.

01:14:30.167 --> 01:14:34.196
And if Kate doesn't like it, she can
bloody well just go... Hey, you. Brian.

01:14:34.296 --> 01:14:37.591
Okay, okay, in the vault.

01:14:39.677 --> 01:14:41.762
Oh, Kate.

01:14:43.889 --> 01:14:45.558
Olivia.

01:14:46.559 --> 01:14:48.436
My best friend.

01:14:49.395 --> 01:14:52.023
Total trust.

01:14:52.148 --> 01:14:54.191
No secrets!

01:14:54.567 --> 01:14:58.529
- We were going to...
- You know what? If you want him, take him.

01:14:58.946 --> 01:15:00.322
But get out of my house.

01:15:01.574 --> 01:15:04.618
Well, now, maybe... okay.

01:15:38.986 --> 01:15:40.654
Thank you.

01:15:41.197 --> 01:15:43.866
Ernesto. Sorry I'm late.

01:15:44.366 --> 01:15:47.912
- Where's your wife?
- Not coming. Sends her regards.

01:15:49.288 --> 01:15:51.691
Okay, strike one, she's not here.

01:15:51.791 --> 01:15:55.361
Strike two, you failed
the recovery program.

01:15:55.461 --> 01:15:58.030
We may be 0-2, but we're going
to swing for the fences

01:15:58.130 --> 01:16:00.466
on the University of Los Angeles.

01:16:00.591 --> 01:16:01.509
Morning, officer Lewis.

01:16:01.634 --> 01:16:04.678
Why has it taken nearly three years
to schedule this interview?

01:16:04.803 --> 01:16:08.140
Well, my client never received
all the notifications from ICE.

01:16:09.350 --> 01:16:12.211
Is this your handwriting, Mr. Haig?

01:16:12.311 --> 01:16:16.090
Some of it is.
Some of it's also my son's.

01:16:16.190 --> 01:16:18.426
Working on his cursive.

01:16:18.526 --> 01:16:20.277
Can you explain this?

01:16:20.653 --> 01:16:24.390
Yes, well, that's not my fault.
Painkillers, dental surgery.

01:16:24.490 --> 01:16:27.935
My client's done 10 sessions of a recovery
program to show his good character.

01:16:28.035 --> 01:16:31.580
Where's the letter of completion?
In the mail, with "bew-locks" written on it?

01:16:32.289 --> 01:16:34.984
It's "bollocks," actually.

01:16:35.084 --> 01:16:37.127
Officer Armstrong!

01:16:42.508 --> 01:16:47.596
Please describe how Mr. Haig
tried to offer you marijuana.

01:16:49.390 --> 01:16:53.352
The other night, as I was leaving
the recovery center,

01:16:53.477 --> 01:16:56.563
Mr. Haig asked me
if I wanted some marijuana.

01:16:58.190 --> 01:17:03.470
Under California law, the possession
of marijuana is a felony.

01:17:03.570 --> 01:17:05.322
That's true.

01:17:05.447 --> 01:17:07.658
What is it you say, Mr. Haig? Cheerios?

01:17:09.618 --> 01:17:12.646
There you have it, the whole sorry saga.

01:17:12.746 --> 01:17:17.501
Ernesto did do one thing
to justify his exorbitant fee.

01:17:18.752 --> 01:17:21.213
He got me this one hour with you.

01:17:22.089 --> 01:17:25.034
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry, Jake.

01:17:25.134 --> 01:17:27.469
- Time's up.
- Jake, please.

01:17:34.601 --> 01:17:36.937
I love you. Do you hear me?
I am so sorry.

01:18:20.230 --> 01:18:22.608
"That is no country for old men.

01:18:25.110 --> 01:18:28.363
The young in one another's arms,

01:18:28.947 --> 01:18:30.808
birds in the trees,

01:18:30.908 --> 01:18:34.745
those dying generations...
at their song."

01:18:35.621 --> 01:18:37.564
So, what's Yeats saying here?

01:18:37.664 --> 01:18:42.277
He's a 60-year-old man looking
at young people screwing and living,

01:18:42.377 --> 01:18:45.422
blissfully unthinking
about their own mortality.

01:18:45.839 --> 01:18:48.258
Yeats knows he's just an aged man,

01:18:49.176 --> 01:18:51.787
but his dreams...

01:18:51.887 --> 01:18:53.847
are of Byzantium.

01:19:00.979 --> 01:19:02.689
- Hello?
- <i>This is Memorial General.</i>

01:19:02.815 --> 01:19:05.484
<i>We need to talk to you
about your father.</i>

01:19:40.852 --> 01:19:44.231
What the buggering hell
are you doing here?

01:19:44.690 --> 01:19:47.025
You hate hospitals.

01:19:47.234 --> 01:19:49.219
You're right.

01:19:49.319 --> 01:19:52.097
I hate bloody hospitals.

01:19:52.197 --> 01:19:55.117
But I love the nurses.

01:20:01.039 --> 01:20:03.333
How's my little Jake?

01:20:06.587 --> 01:20:08.880
He's all right, Dad.

01:20:10.382 --> 01:20:12.426
You know, I...

01:20:13.802 --> 01:20:17.097
I don't think I could have done
what you did.

01:20:18.640 --> 01:20:23.353
You stuck with that boy
through all the muck and bullets.

01:20:26.106 --> 01:20:29.067
You're a better man than I, Gunga Din.

01:20:34.364 --> 01:20:36.783
I don't know about that, Dad.

01:20:37.743 --> 01:20:41.705
You still shagging the...
Yank totty's sister, are we?

01:20:41.830 --> 01:20:44.041
No, I blew that one.

01:20:46.418 --> 01:20:49.529
Threw away a pearl beyond price.

01:20:49.629 --> 01:20:53.342
Totty and Totty's sister.

01:20:53.467 --> 01:20:57.012
None of us are talking.
It's all a big mess.

01:21:04.561 --> 01:21:09.232
Marvelous bloody place,
though, isn't it? Californ-i-a?

01:21:10.776 --> 01:21:15.781
Sunshine, beaches, and girls. Yeah.

01:21:17.157 --> 01:21:19.242
Marijuana.

01:21:19.367 --> 01:21:22.954
God, how the buggering hell
did I miss out on all that for so long?

01:21:23.538 --> 01:21:25.457
You came.

01:21:26.041 --> 01:21:28.251
You saw it once.

01:21:31.088 --> 01:21:34.174
It all goes so fast.

01:21:36.051 --> 01:21:39.304
These buggers here,
they don't think I've got long.

01:21:42.265 --> 01:21:43.892
Well...

01:21:44.184 --> 01:21:46.353
it's all a load of bollocks, really.

01:21:46.937 --> 01:21:48.647
What is?

01:21:49.940 --> 01:21:54.027
You know, there's nothing honorable
in misery, Richard.

01:21:55.028 --> 01:21:57.723
Carpe diem.

01:21:57.823 --> 01:22:01.368
Boff and be merry.

01:22:01.868 --> 01:22:05.731
Now, listen. You listen to me carefully.

01:22:05.831 --> 01:22:11.419
This might be the most important
bit of advice I'll ever give you.

01:22:16.299 --> 01:22:18.552
For God's sake, man...

01:22:18.677 --> 01:22:21.346
go and get your bloody girl.

01:22:21.805 --> 01:22:23.682
Go on.

01:22:24.391 --> 01:22:26.434
Bugger off.

01:22:38.655 --> 01:22:40.657
Hey, Richard.

01:22:43.034 --> 01:22:45.328
You remember my epitaph.

01:22:47.163 --> 01:22:49.124
Of course I do, Dad.

01:22:50.500 --> 01:22:52.711
Of course I do.

01:23:54.481 --> 01:23:57.942
Byzantium is the place he longs for.

01:23:58.276 --> 01:24:00.595
He needs to make this journey.

01:24:00.695 --> 01:24:04.224
I'm going to sort this all out.
I promise you. Okay, Jake?

01:24:04.324 --> 01:24:05.784
<i>How?</i>

01:24:08.161 --> 01:24:10.330
I'll Skype you tomorrow, okay?

01:24:18.546 --> 01:24:20.090
Is she talking to Olivia yet?

01:24:20.215 --> 01:24:23.426
<i>Olivia's book launches here next week.
Kate isn't even going.</i>

01:24:24.302 --> 01:24:27.764
- <i>She's icing everyone out, even me.</i>
- All right.

01:24:28.264 --> 01:24:29.624
See ya, Brian.

01:24:29.724 --> 01:24:32.585
Yeats knows that unless
he makes this journey,

01:24:32.685 --> 01:24:36.940
unless he defies logic and authority,

01:24:37.148 --> 01:24:41.986
unless his soul claps hands
and sings out loud...

01:24:44.864 --> 01:24:47.242
he is nothing more...

01:24:47.951 --> 01:24:51.329
than a tattered coat upon a stick.

01:25:19.524 --> 01:25:21.943
You old bugger.

01:25:25.154 --> 01:25:28.032
There is a country for old men.

01:25:30.702 --> 01:25:32.871
If not now, when?

01:25:34.122 --> 01:25:39.294
Ernesto, Richard Haig. <i>Cómo está?</i>

01:26:35.600 --> 01:26:38.144
<i>Adios! Adios, amigos.</i>

01:26:48.905 --> 01:26:51.449
- Hey, Dad.
- <i>Hi, Jakey.</i>

01:26:51.574 --> 01:26:53.701
<i>Go to the door and tell me what you see.</i>

01:26:53.826 --> 01:26:55.578
Okay.

01:27:03.252 --> 01:27:07.423
Oh, look at you, boy! Oh, look at you.

01:27:07.548 --> 01:27:09.300
Richie!

01:27:12.011 --> 01:27:15.598
Thank God you're here, dude.
Thank God. Thank God.

01:27:15.723 --> 01:27:19.018
- You can let go now, Brian. That's okay.
- Okay. All right. Okay.

01:27:20.019 --> 01:27:22.397
Can you believe it, Mom?
He's really here.

01:27:22.688 --> 01:27:26.192
- Hi, Kate.
- Hey, how did you get here?

01:27:26.317 --> 01:27:29.220
I just came across the border.
It's an old trick of mine.

01:27:29.320 --> 01:27:33.141
- What if you get caught?
- I won't. I'll be gone before they know it.

01:27:33.241 --> 01:27:37.937
Remember my lawyer, Ernesto? He's going
to sort this whole mess out, okay?

01:27:38.037 --> 01:27:39.647
- Yay!
- Don't you worry.

01:27:39.747 --> 01:27:41.816
It's only going to cost me a fortune.

01:27:41.916 --> 01:27:45.278
And look, Kate,
we can't keep going like this.

01:27:45.378 --> 01:27:49.924
I mean, Jake, he needs his mom
and dad to be adults, right?

01:27:50.424 --> 01:27:52.093
Yeah.

01:27:53.344 --> 01:27:56.706
Look, I'm sorry. I'm sorry we hurt you.

01:27:56.806 --> 01:28:00.935
Olivia wanted to tell you,
and it was my fault she didn't.

01:28:01.435 --> 01:28:05.298
But you're sisters. Come on.
Cut her some slack.

01:28:05.398 --> 01:28:07.900
Life is so short, Kate.

01:28:08.609 --> 01:28:11.779
Like my dad used to say, carpe diem.

01:28:11.904 --> 01:28:14.532
Let's boff and be merry?

01:28:16.826 --> 01:28:19.353
- Okay.
- Great.

01:28:19.453 --> 01:28:22.748
Great. And... one last thing.

01:28:23.166 --> 01:28:26.586
- Can I take a shower, please?
- He really stinks.

01:28:27.962 --> 01:28:33.159
Thank you, everybody, for coming.
I would like to thank my agent,

01:28:33.259 --> 01:28:34.827
Tim Prince.

01:28:34.927 --> 01:28:37.914
I would also like to thank my...

01:28:38.014 --> 01:28:41.125
ex brother-in-law, Richard.

01:28:41.225 --> 01:28:44.670
He was the inspiration
for the burnt-out,

01:28:44.770 --> 01:28:49.066
recovering-alcoholic cop
who saves the day.

01:28:49.525 --> 01:28:52.236
Although he doesn't know it,
so let's not tell him.

01:28:53.195 --> 01:28:58.159
And, lastly, I would like to thank
somebody very special to me

01:28:58.284 --> 01:29:01.020
who couldn't be here today,

01:29:01.120 --> 01:29:05.041
which is nobody's fault but mine.

01:29:32.526 --> 01:29:34.904
All right. Here we are.

01:29:48.125 --> 01:29:49.794
Hey.

01:29:53.881 --> 01:29:57.118
I'm so sorry. So sorry.

01:29:57.218 --> 01:29:59.203
I'm sorry, too.

01:29:59.303 --> 01:30:01.764
Let's never fight again, okay?

01:30:02.848 --> 01:30:04.684
Come here.

01:30:13.484 --> 01:30:16.862
- Let's go back inside.
- Just give me a minute, all right?

01:30:16.987 --> 01:30:18.656
Okay.

01:30:28.833 --> 01:30:30.584
Hi.

01:30:31.919 --> 01:30:35.965
- You came.
- I came. Piece of cake.

01:30:39.635 --> 01:30:42.138
I came because I love you.

01:30:43.556 --> 01:30:45.975
I came because I need you.

01:30:47.351 --> 01:30:49.603
I need my son.

01:30:49.728 --> 01:30:51.981
I need my family.

01:30:52.106 --> 01:30:54.150
That's why I came.

01:30:56.360 --> 01:30:59.680
- You want to hear something crazy?
- What?

01:30:59.780 --> 01:31:01.323
I knew you'd come.

01:31:01.449 --> 01:31:04.660
- It's irrational.
- It's romantic.

01:31:05.369 --> 01:31:07.396
You and I...

01:31:07.496 --> 01:31:11.542
we've only had moments.
Now we have time.

01:31:35.858 --> 01:31:40.738
I spent my whole life
in opposition to this man.

01:31:41.947 --> 01:31:44.825
Honestly, he never did
a bloody thing for me,

01:31:45.743 --> 01:31:47.870
except this.

01:31:49.455 --> 01:31:52.374
Asking me to scatter his ashes here.

01:31:55.294 --> 01:31:57.671
And it saved my life,

01:31:59.173 --> 01:32:02.509
because it brought me back to the people
I love most in this world.

01:32:09.516 --> 01:32:13.020
- Even you, Brian.
- You're the man, Richard.

01:32:13.395 --> 01:32:17.341
There comes a time, and there's always
a time, and I guess this is the time.

01:32:17.441 --> 01:32:21.487
So, Jakey, shall we set grandpa free?

01:32:30.204 --> 01:32:32.247
Okay, Dad.

01:32:32.873 --> 01:32:35.167
Enjoy paradise.

01:32:42.758 --> 01:32:45.536
So how long are you staying?

01:32:45.636 --> 01:32:48.289
Okay, Jakey, listen to me here.

01:32:48.389 --> 01:32:50.641
I have to sort out a few things first.

01:32:52.393 --> 01:32:54.211
But...

01:32:54.311 --> 01:32:57.940
maybe marrying your aunt might help.

01:33:00.150 --> 01:33:03.696
- What?
- Well, I am down on one knee.

01:33:06.990 --> 01:33:09.993
Then get up and kiss me again.

01:33:28.554 --> 01:33:31.932
<i>Up and away we set off</i>

01:33:32.558 --> 01:33:36.270
<i>Secretly scared we'd get lost</i>

01:33:36.770 --> 01:33:40.799
<i>Up in the clouds, over the town</i>

01:33:40.899 --> 01:33:44.111
<i>Beyond the wall</i>

01:33:44.903 --> 01:33:48.490
<i>Some of us knew we might fall</i>

01:33:49.074 --> 01:33:52.619
<i>Under the weight of it all</i>

01:33:52.995 --> 01:33:57.107
<i>And though we'd been warned
of the oncoming storms</i>

01:33:57.207 --> 01:34:00.169
<i>Still we stood tall</i>

01:34:01.295 --> 01:34:05.174
<i>Soar from the moonlight</i>

01:34:05.299 --> 01:34:09.386
<i>Straight to the sunrise</i>

01:34:09.511 --> 01:34:13.348
<i>This will be our time</i>

01:34:13.474 --> 01:34:17.711
<i>To free-fall and nose-dive</i>

01:34:17.811 --> 01:34:21.690
<i>Out of the black night</i>

01:34:21.815 --> 01:34:25.594
<i>Into the bright light</i>

01:34:25.694 --> 01:34:29.615
<i>With the whole world in our sight</i>

01:34:29.740 --> 01:34:34.119
<i>Like a miniature paradise</i>

01:34:36.246 --> 01:34:38.290
<i>Yeah</i>

01:34:50.344 --> 01:34:53.847
<i>My shadow is cast on the ground</i>

01:34:54.473 --> 01:34:58.310
<i>I'm flying too fast to look down</i>

01:34:58.560 --> 01:35:00.671
<i>At the rooftops and trees</i>

01:35:00.771 --> 01:35:05.692
<i>And my family waving at me</i>

